-----

Above student answer is wrong. 61C doesn't fulfill the natural science elective for EECS majors, but rather, the physical science breadth requirement for L&S majors. Also I wouldn't suggest loading up on another tech/tech-like class if you're taking 61B + 2 techs in the fall, 61B with Hilfinger is a lot of (project) work.
